{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881539469,"sessionID":"ses_285365f84ffeZDEPNqZyERjCgJ","part":{"id":"prt_d7ac9bfbf001oVP55CHFoQEx6d","messageID":"msg_d7ac9b439001AAA4R4FTm9Sd4v","sessionID":"ses_285365f84ffeZDEPNqZyERjCgJ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_73ff32b8a271456bbba0611b","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-031/tasks.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-031/tasks.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) Tasks\n2: \n3: **Module:** manifests  \n4: **Language:** YAML  \n5: **Size:** M  \n6: **Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Phase 1: WorkloadManager RBAC\n11: \n12: - [ ] **T1.1** Create WorkloadManager ServiceAccount\n13:   - Set `apiVersion: v1`, `kind: ServiceAccount`\n14:   - Name: `workloadmanager`\n15:   - Set namespace to `{{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n16:   - Add standard labels (optional)\n17:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n18:   - Verify: `kubectl get sa/workloadmanager -n <namespace>` succeeds\n19: \n20: - [ ] **T1.2** Create WorkloadManager ClusterRole\n21:   - Set `apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1`, `kind: ClusterRole`\n22:   - Name: `workloadmanager`\n23:   - Add rule for `agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxes`: full CRUD (get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete)\n24:   - Add rule for `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxclaims`: full CRUD\n25:   - Add rule for `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxtemplates`: full CRUD\n26:   - Add rule for `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxwarmpools`: full CRUD\n27:   - Add rule for `extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxwarmpools/status`: get, update, patch\n28:   - Add rule for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters`: full CRUD\n29:   - Add rule for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters/status`: get, update, patch\n30:   - Add rule for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/codeinterpreters/finalizers`: update\n31:   - Add rule for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/agentruntimes`: get, list, watch\n32:   - Add rule for `runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh/agentruntimes/status`: update, patch\n33:   - Add rule for core `pods`: get, list, watch\n34:   - Add rule for `authentication.k8s.io/tokenreviews`: create\n35:   - Add rule for core `secrets`: full CRUD\n36:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n37:   - Verify: `kubectl get clusterrole/workloadmanager` shows all rules\n38: \n39: - [ ] **T1.3** Create WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding\n40:   - Set `apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1`, `kind: ClusterRoleBinding`\n41:   - Name: `workloadmanager`\n42:   - Reference roleRef: `apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io`, `kind: ClusterRole`, `name: workloadmanager`\n43:   - Reference subject: `kind: ServiceAccount`, `name: workloadmanager`, `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n44:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n45:   - Verify: `kubectl get clusterrolebinding/workloadmanager` shows correct roleRef and subjects\n46: \n47: ---\n48: \n49: ## Phase 2: Router RBAC (Optional)\n50: \n51: - [ ] **T2.1** Create Router ServiceAccount (conditional)\n52:   - Guard with `{{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}`\n53:   - Set `apiVersion: v1`, `kind: ServiceAccount`\n54:   - Name: `{{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}`\n55:   - Set namespace to `{{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n56:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n57:   - Verify: ServiceAccount renders only when `router.rbac.create=true`\n58: \n59: - [ ] **T2.2** Create Router Role (namespace-scoped)\n60:   - Guard with `{{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}`\n61:   - Set `apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1`, `kind: Role`\n62:   - Name: `{{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}`\n63:   - Namespace: `{{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n64:   - Add rule for core `secrets`: full CRUD (get, list, watch, create, update, patch, delete)\n65:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n66:   - Verify: Role is namespace-scoped (not ClusterRole)\n67: \n68: - [ ] **T2.3** Create Router RoleBinding\n69:   - Guard with `{{- if .Values.router.rbac.create }}`\n70:   - Set `apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1`, `kind: RoleBinding`\n71:   - Name: `{{ .Values.router.serviceAccountName | default \"agentcube-router\" }}`\n72:   - Namespace: `{{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n73:   - Reference roleRef: `apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io`, `kind: Role`, `name: <router SA name>`\n74:   - Reference subject: `kind: ServiceAccount`, `name: <router SA name>`, `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n75:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml`\n76:   - Verify: RoleBinding connects Router SA to Router Role within namespace\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: ## Phase 3: Volcano Agent Scheduler RBAC (Optional)\n81: \n82: - [ ] **T3.1** Create Volcano ServiceAccount (conditional)\n83:   - Guard with `{{- if .Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled }}`\n84:   - Set `apiVersion: v1`, `kind: ServiceAccount`\n85:   - Name: `volcano-agent-scheduler`\n86:   - Namespace: `{{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n87:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n88:   - Verify: ServiceAccount renders only when `volcano.scheduler.enabled=true`\n89: \n90: - [ ] **T3.2** Create Volcano ClusterRole\n91:   - Guard with `{{- if .Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled }}`\n92:   - Set `apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1`, `kind: ClusterRole`\n93:   - Name: `volcano-agent-scheduler`\n94:   - Add rule for `apiextensions.k8s.io/customresourcedefinitions`: create, get, list, watch, delete\n95:   - Add rule for core `events`: create, list, watch, update, patch\n96:   - Add rule for core `pods`: get, list, watch, patch, delete\n97:   - Add rule for core `pods/status`: update\n98:   - Add rule for core `pods/binding`: create\n99:   - Add rule for core `persistentvolumeclaims`: list, watch, update\n100:   - Add rule for core `persistentvolumes`: list, watch, update\n101:   - Add rule for core `namespaces`: list, watch, get\n102:   - Add rule for core `services`: list, watch, get\n103:   - Add rule for core `replicationcontrollers`: list, watch, get\n104:   - Add rule for core `resourcequotas`: list, watch\n105:   - Add rule for core `nodes`: get, list, watch, update, patch\n106:   - Add rule for `storage.k8s.io/storageclasses`: list, watch\n107:   - Add rule for `storage.k8s.io/csinodes`: list, watch\n108:   - Add rule for `storage.k8s.io/csidrivers`: list, watch\n109:   - Add rule for `storage.k8s.io/csistoragecapacities`: list, watch\n110:   - Add rule for `storage.k8s.io/volumeattachments`: list, watch\n111:   - Add rule for `policy/poddisruptionbudgets`: list, watch\n112:   - Add rule for `scheduling.k8s.io/priorityclasses`: get, list, watch\n113:   - Add rule for `scheduling.incubator.k8s.io/podgroups`: list, watch, update\n114:   - Add rule for `scheduling.volcano.sh/podgroups`: list, watch, update\n115:   - Add rule for core `configmaps`: get, list, watch, create, delete, update\n116:   - Add rule for `apps/daemonsets`: list, watch, get\n117:   - Add rule for `apps/replicasets`: list, watch, get\n118:   - Add rule for `apps/statefulsets`: list, watch, get\n119:   - Add rule for `coordination.k8s.io/leases`: get, create, update, watch\n120:   - Add rule for `resource.k8s.io/resourceclaims`: get, list, watch, create, update, patch\n121:   - Add rule for `resource.k8s.io/resourceclaims/status`: update\n122:   - Add rule for `resource.k8s.io/deviceclasses`: get, list, watch, create\n123:   - Add rule for `resource.k8s.io/resourceslices`: get, list, watch, create\n124:   - Add rule for `shard.volcano.sh/nodeshards`: list, watch, get, update\n125:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n126:   - Verify: ClusterRole has comprehensive scheduling permissions\n127: \n128: - [ ] **T3.3** Create Volcano ClusterRoleBinding\n129:   - Guard with `{{- if .Values.volcano.scheduler.enabled }}`\n130:   - Set `apiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1`, `kind: ClusterRoleBinding`\n131:   - Name: `volcano-agent-scheduler-role`\n132:   - Reference roleRef: `apiGroup: rbac.authorization.k8s.io`, `kind: ClusterRole`, `name: volcano-agent-scheduler`\n133:   - Reference subject: `kind: ServiceAccount`, `name: volcano-agent-scheduler`, `namespace: {{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n134:   - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml`\n135:   - Verify: Binding connects Volcano SA to ClusterRole\n136: \n137: ---\n138: \n139: ## Phase 4: RBAC Validation\n140: \n141: - [ ] **T4.1** Test WorkloadManager RBAC with helm template\n142:   - Command: `helm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"redis:6379\"`\n143:   - Verify: ServiceAccount/workloadmanager present in output\n144:   - Verify: ClusterRole/workloadmanager present with all rules\n145:   - Verify: ClusterRoleBinding/workloadmanager present with correct references\n146: \n147: - [ ] **T4.2** Test Router RBAC disabled by default\n148:   - Command: `helm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"redis:6379\"`\n149:   - Verify: No Router ServiceAccount in output\n150:   - Verify: No Router Role in output\n151:   - Verify: No Router RoleBinding in output\n152: \n153: - [ ] **T4.3** Test Router RBAC enabled\n154:   - Command: `helm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"redis:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true`\n155:   - Verify: ServiceAccount/agentcube-router present\n156:   - Verify: Role/agentcube-router present with secrets permissions\n157:   - Verify: RoleBinding/agentcube-router present\n158: \n159: - [ ] **T4.4** Test Router RBAC with custom serviceAccountName\n160:   - Command: `helm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"redis:6379\" --set router.rbac.create=true --set router.serviceAccountName=custom-router`\n161:   - Verify: ServiceAccount/custom-router present\n162:   - Verify: Role/custom-router present\n163:   - Verify: RoleBinding/custom-router present with correct references\n164: \n165: - [ ] **T4.5** Test Volcano RBAC disabled by default\n166:   - Command: `helm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"redis:6379\"`\n167:   - Verify: No Volcano ServiceAccount in output\n168:   - Verify: No Volcano ClusterRole in output\n169:   - Verify: No Volcano ClusterRoleBinding in output\n170: \n171: - [ ] **T4.6** Test Volcano RBAC enabled\n172:   - Command: `helm template test manifests/charts/base --set redis.addr=\"redis:6379\" --set volcano.scheduler.enabled=true`\n173:   - Verify: ServiceAccount/volcano-agent-scheduler present\n174:   - Verify: ClusterRole/volcano-agent-scheduler present with scheduling permissions\n175:   - Verify: ClusterRoleBinding/volcano-agent-scheduler-role present\n176: \n177: - [ ] **T4.7** Validate YAML syntax\n178:   - Command: `helm lint manifests/charts/base`\n179:   - Verify: No RBAC-related errors or warnings\n180: \n181: - [ ] **T4.8** Apply RBAC to test cluster (optional)\n182:   - Command: `kubectl apply -f manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml --namespace=test`\n183:   - Command: `kubectl apply -f manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac-router.yaml --namespace=test` (with values override)\n184:   - Command: `kubectl apply -f manifests/charts/base/templates/volcano-agent-scheduler-development.yaml --namespace=test` (with values override)\n185:   - Verify: All RBAC resources created successfully\n186: \n187: - [ ] **T4.9** Verify WorkloadManager permissions\n188:   - Command: `kubectl auth can-i --as=system:serviceaccount:<namespace>:workloadmanager --list --namespace=test`\n189:   - Verify: Expected permissions listed for sandboxes, codeinterpreters, secrets, etc.\n190: \n191: - [ ] **T4.10** Verify Router permissions (when enabled)\n192:   - Command: `kubectl auth can-i --as=system:serviceaccount:<namespace>:agentcube-router --list --namespace=test`\n193:   - Verify: Secrets CRUD permissions in namespace\n194: \n195: - [ ] **T4.11** Verify Volcano permissions (when enabled)\n196:   - Command: `kubectl auth can-i --as=system:serviceaccount:<namespace>:volcano-agent-scheduler --list --namespace=test`\n197:   - Verify: Scheduling permissions for pods, nodes, podgroups, etc.\n198: \n199: ---\n200: \n201: ## Acceptance Criteria\n202: \n203: 1. ✅ WorkloadManager ServiceAccount created in release namespace\n204: 2. ✅ WorkloadManager ClusterRole has full CRUD for sandbox-related CRDs\n205: 3. ✅ WorkloadManager ClusterRole has status update permissions for codeinterpreters and agentruntimes\n206: 4. ✅ WorkloadManager ClusterRole has finalizer update permission for codeinterpreters\n207: 5. ✅ WorkloadManager ClusterRole has tokenreviews create for authentication\n208: 6. ✅ WorkloadManager ClusterRoleBinding correctly binds SA to ClusterRole\n209: 7. ✅ Router RBAC is optional (disabled by default)\n210: 8. ✅ Router RBAC uses namespace-scoped Role (not ClusterRole)\n211: 9. ✅ Router RBAC limited to secrets management\n212: 10. ✅ Router serviceAccountName is configurable via values\n213: 11. ✅ Volcano RBAC is optional (disabled by default)\n214: 12. ✅ Volcano ClusterRole has comprehensive scheduling permissions\n215: 13. ✅ Volcano ClusterRoleBinding correctly binds SA to ClusterRole\n216: 14. ✅ All conditional rendering works correctly via helm template\n217: 15. ✅ `helm lint` passes with no RBAC-related errors\n218: 16. ✅ RBAC resources apply successfully to test cluster\n219: 17. ✅ `kubectl auth can-i` confirms expected permissions for each SA\n220: 18. ✅ RBAC follows least-privilege principle (each SA has only necessary permissions)\n221: 19. ✅ All manifests use Helm templating for namespace consistency\n222: 20. ✅ RBAC configuration matches AR-030 Phase 6 and Phase 7 specifications\n223: \n224: ---\n225: \n226: **Notes:**\n227: - Stage ST-3: Implementation complete (templates exist in codebase)\n228: - WorkloadManager RBAC: Always installed (core component)\n229: - Router RBAC: Optional, controlled by `router.rbac.create` (default: false)\n230: - Volcano RBAC: Optional, controlled by `volcano.scheduler.enabled` (default: false)\n231: - WorkloadManager uses ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding (cluster-wide permissions required)\n232: - Router uses Role/RoleBinding (namespace-scoped, secrets only)\n233: - Volcano uses ClusterRole/ClusterRoleBinding (cluster-wide scheduling permissions)\n234: - All templates use `{{ .Release.Namespace }}` for namespace consistency\n235: - Router serviceAccountName configurable via `router.serviceAccountName` values key\n\n(End of file - total 235 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-031 — RBAC 配置 (SA/Role/Binding) Tasks\n\n**Module:** manifests  \n**Language:** YAML  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: WorkloadManager RBAC\n\n- [ ] **T1.1** Create WorkloadManager ServiceAccount\n  - Set `apiVersion: v1`, `kind: ServiceAccount`\n  - Name: `workloadmanager`\n  - Set namespace to `{{ .Release.Namespace }}`\n  - Add standard labels (optional)\n  - File: `manifests/charts/base/templates/rbac/workloadmanager.yaml`\n  - Verify: `kubectl get sa/workloadmanager -n <namespace>` succeeds\n\n- [ ] **T1.2** Create WorkloadManager ClusterRole","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-031/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775881539441,"end":1775881539467}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881539473,"sessionID":"ses_285365f84ffeZDEPNqZyERjCgJ","part":{"id":"prt_d7ac9c55d001AoZXZxaYhRyNF0","messageID":"msg_d7ac9b439001AAA4R4FTm9Sd4v","sessionID":"ses_285365f84ffeZDEPNqZyERjCgJ","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_57dd8f24df0d4d729e348f01","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/docker/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/docker/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Docker Multi-Stage Build Design — AR-032\n2: \n3: **Module:** `docker`  \n4: **Language:** Dockerfile  \n5: **Size:** S  \n6: **Stage:** ST-1 completed\n7: \n8: ---\n9: \n10: ## Overview\n11: \n12: This document describes the technical implementation details for Docker multi-stage builds for three AgentCube components: Workload Manager, Router, and picod. The design follows container security best practices, optimizes for minimal image size, and ensures consistency across development, testing, and production environments.\n13: \n14: ---\n15: \n16: ## Architecture\n17: \n18: ### Multi-Stage Build Pattern\n19: \n20: Each component uses a two-stage Dockerfile:\n21: \n22: ```\n23: ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n24: │  Stage 1: Builder                   │\n25: │  - Base: golang:1.21-alpine         │\n26: │  - Downloads Go modules             │\n27: │  - Compiles static binary           │\n28: │  - CGO_ENABLED=0                    │\n29: └─────────────────────────────────────┘\n30:                   │\n31:                   ▼\n32: ┌─────────────────────────────────────┐\n33: │  Stage 2: Runtime                   │\n34: │  - Base: alpine:3.19                │\n35: │  - Copies binary from builder       │\n36: │  - Non-root user (UID 1000)         │\n37: │  - Exposes port 8080                │\n38: └─────────────────────────────────────┘\n39: ```\n40: \n41: ### Component Mapping\n42: \n43: | Component | Dockerfile | Source Path | Binary Output | Runtime User |\n44: |-----------|------------|-------------|---------------|--------------|\n45: | Workload Manager | `docker/Dockerfile` | `./cmd/workload-manager` | `/workloadmanager` | `apiserver` (UID 1000) |\n46: | Router | `docker/Dockerfile.router` | `./cmd/router` | `/router` | `router` (UID 1000) |\n47: | Picod | `docker/Dockerfile.picod` | `./cmd/picod` | `/picod` | `picod` (UID 1000) |\n48: \n49: ---\n50: \n51: ## Data Structures\n52: \n53: ### Docker Build Arguments\n54: \n55: ```dockerfile\n56: # Common to all Dockerfiles\n57: ARG GO_VERSION=1.21\n58: ARG ALPINE_VERSION=3.19\n59: ARG TARGETARCH=amd64\n60: ARG TARGETOS=linux\n61: ```\n62: \n63: ### OCI Image Labels\n64: \n65: ```dockerfile\n66: # Applied to all images\n67: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.title=\"<component>\"\n68: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.description=\"AgentCube <component> component\"\n69: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.vendor=\"AgentCube\"\n70: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.version=\"<version>\"\n71: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.revision=\"<commit-sha>\"\n72: ```\n73: \n74: ### Environment Variables (Runtime)\n75: \n76: | Variable | Component | Purpose | Required |\n77: |----------|-----------|---------|----------|\n78: | `REDIS_ADDR` | Workload Manager, Router | Redis server address | Yes |\n79: | `REDIS_PASSWORD` | Workload Manager, Router | Redis authentication | No (default: \"\") |\n80: | `WORKLOAD_MANAGER_URL` | Router | Workload Manager endpoint | Yes |\n81: | `PORT` | All | HTTP listen port | No (default: 8080) |\n82: | `AGENTCUBE_NAMESPACE` | All | Kubernetes namespace | No (auto-injected via fieldRef) |\n83: \n84: ---\n85: \n86: ## API Contracts\n87: \n88: ### Docker Build Interface\n89: \n90: **Build Command:**\n91: ```bash\n92: docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.<component> -t <image-name>:<tag> .\n93: ```\n94: \n95: **Build Context:** Repository root\n96: \n97: **Required Files in Context:**\n98: - `go.mod`, `go.sum`\n99: - `cmd/<component>/`\n100: - `pkg/`\n101: \n102: **Excluded Files (via `.dockerignore`):**\n103: - `.git/`\n104: - `bin/`, `pkg/` (build artifacts)\n105: - `*_test.go`\n106: - `*.md` (documentation)\n107: - `testing/`\n108: - `.pytest_cache/`, `__pycache__/`\n109: \n110: ### Container Runtime Interface\n111: \n112: **Exposed Port:** 8080 (all components)\n113: \n114: **Entrypoint:**\n115: - Workload Manager: `/workloadmanager`\n116: - Router: `/router`\n117: - Picod: `/picod`\n118: \n119: **Default CMD:**\n120: - Workload Manager: `[\"--port=8080\"]`\n121: - Router: `[\"--port=8080\", \"--debug\"]`\n122: - Picod: `[\"--port=8080\"]`\n123: \n124: **Health Check:**\n125: ```dockerfile\n126: HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=3s --start-period=5s --retries=3 \\\n127:     CMD wget --no-verbose --tries=1 --spider http://localhost:8080/health || exit 1\n128: ```\n129: \n130: ---\n131: \n132: ## Error Handling\n133: \n134: ### Build-Time Errors\n135: \n136: | Error | Cause | Resolution |\n137: |-------|-------|------------|\n138: | `go.mod not found` | Build context incorrect | Ensure build runs from repository root |\n139: | `build failed: package not found` | Source path mismatch | Verify `cmd/` and `pkg/` are in context |\n140: | `out of memory` | Insufficient builder resources | Increase Docker memory limit |\n141: | `COPY failed: file not found` | `.dockerignore` excludes required file | Review `.dockerignore` patterns |\n142: \n143: ### Runtime Errors\n144: \n145: | Error | Cause | Resolution |\n146: |-------|-------|------------|\n147: | `permission denied` | Running as root when non-root expected | Ensure `USER` directive is applied |\n148: | `port already in use` | Port 8080 occupied | Override `PORT` environment variable |\n149: | `connection refused to Redis` | `REDIS_ADDR` not set or incorrect | Verify environment variable configuration |\n150: | `binary not found` | Build stage failed to produce binary | Check builder stage logs |\n151: \n152: ### Validation Failures\n153: \n154: The `validate.sh` script shall fail with non-zero exit code when:\n155: - Image size ≥ 50MB\n156: - Layer count > 5\n157: - Running as root user\n158: - Port 8080 not exposed\n159: - Health check not configured\n160: \n161: ---\n162: \n163: ## Testing Strategy\n164: \n165: ### Unit Tests (Dockerfile Syntax)\n166: \n167: **Test File:** `docker/Dockerfile.test` (optional linting stage)\n168: \n169: **Test Cases:**\n170: 1. All Dockerfiles pass `hadolint` validation\n171: 2. No hardcoded secrets in any layer\n172: 3. Base images use pinned versions (not `latest`)\n173: \n174: ### Integration Tests\n175: \n176: **Test Script:** `docker/test/build_test.sh`\n177: \n178: ```bash\n179: #!/bin/bash\n180: # Build all images and verify basic properties\n181: \n182: set -e\n183: \n184: IMAGES=(\n185:     \"workloadmanager:test\"\n186:     \"router:test\"\n187:     \"picod:test\"\n188: )\n189: \n190: for image in \"${IMAGES[@]}\"; do\n191:     echo \"Building $image...\"\n192:     docker build -f \"docker/Dockerfile.${image%%:*}\" -t \"$image\" .\n193:     \n194:     # Verify image exists\n195:     docker image inspect \"$image\" > /dev/null\n196:     \n197:     echo \"✓ $image built successfully\"\n198: done\n199: ```\n200: \n201: ### Container Runtime Tests\n202: \n203: **Test Script:** `docker/test/runtime_test.sh`\n204: \n205: ```bash\n206: #!/bin/bash\n207: # Test container runtime behavior\n208: \n209: set -e\n210: \n211: test_container() {\n212:     local image=$1\n213:     local name=$2\n214:     \n215:     # Start container\n216:     docker run -d --name \"$name\" \"$image\"\n217:     \n218:     # Wait for health check\n219:     sleep 10\n220:     \n221:     # Check running status\n222:     if ! docker inspect --format='{{.State.Running}}' \"$name\" | grep -q true; then\n223:         echo \"✗ $name failed to start\"\n224:         docker logs \"$name\"\n225:         return 1\n226:     fi\n227:     \n228:     # Check non-root user\n229:     local user=$(docker exec \"$name\" id -u)\n230:     if [ \"$user\" != \"1000\" ]; then\n231:         echo \"✗ $name running as root (UID: $user)\"\n232:         return 1\n233:     fi\n234:     \n235:     # Cleanup\n236:     docker stop \"$name\" && docker rm \"$name\"\n237:     \n238:     echo \"✓ $name passed runtime tests\"\n239: }\n240: \n241: test_container \"workloadmanager:test\" \"wm-test\"\n242: test_container \"router:test\" \"router-test\"\n243: test_container \"picod:test\" \"picod-test\"\n244: ```\n245: \n246: ### Security Tests\n247: \n248: **Tool:** Trivy (optional)\n249: \n250: ```bash\n251: # Scan for vulnerabilities\n252: trivy image workloadmanager:latest --severity HIGH,CRITICAL --exit-code 1\n253: trivy image router:latest --severity HIGH,CRITICAL --exit-code 1\n254: trivy image picod:latest --severity HIGH,CRITICAL --exit-code 1\n255: ```\n256: \n257: ### Performance Tests\n258: \n259: **Metrics to Validate:**\n260: - Build time < 5 minutes per image (with cached dependencies)\n261: - Image size < 50MB per image\n262: - Layer count ≤ 5\n263: - Container start time < 2 seconds\n264: \n265: ---\n266: \n267: ## Implementation Details\n268: \n269: ### Workload Manager Dockerfile\n270: \n271: ```dockerfile\n272: # docker/Dockerfile\n273: # Multi-stage build for Workload Manager\n274: \n275: # Stage 1: Builder\n276: FROM golang:1.21-alpine AS builder\n277: \n278: WORKDIR /build\n279: \n280: # Cache Go modules\n281: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n282: RUN go mod download\n283: \n284: # Copy source code\n285: COPY cmd/workload-manager ./cmd/workload-manager\n286: COPY pkg ./pkg\n287: \n288: # Build static binary\n289: RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build \\\n290:     -ldflags=\"-w -s\" \\\n291:     -o /build/workloadmanager \\\n292:     ./cmd/workload-manager\n293: \n294: # Stage 2: Runtime\n295: FROM alpine:3.19 AS runtime\n296: \n297: # Install CA certificates for HTTPS\n298: RUN apk --no-cache add ca-certificates\n299: \n300: WORKDIR /app\n301: \n302: # Copy binary from builder\n303: COPY --from=builder /build/workloadmanager /app/workloadmanager\n304: \n305: # Create non-root user\n306: RUN adduser -D -u 1000 apiserver\n307: \n308: # Set ownership\n309: RUN chown -R apiserver:apiserver /app\n310: \n311: # Switch to non-root user\n312: USER apiserver\n313: \n314: # Expose port\n315: EXPOSE 8080\n316: \n317: # Health check\n318: HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=3s --start-period=5s --retries=3 \\\n319:     CMD wget --no-verbose --tries=1 --spider http://localhost:8080/health || exit 1\n320: \n321: # Labels\n322: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.title=\"workloadmanager\"\n323: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.description=\"AgentCube Workload Manager component\"\n324: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.vendor=\"AgentCube\"\n325: \n326: # Entrypoint\n327: ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/workloadmanager\"]\n328: CMD [\"--port=8080\"]\n329: ```\n330: \n331: ### Router Dockerfile\n332: \n333: ```dockerfile\n334: # docker/Dockerfile.router\n335: # Multi-stage build for Router\n336: \n337: # Stage 1: Builder\n338: FROM golang:1.21-alpine AS builder\n339: \n340: WORKDIR /build\n341: \n342: # Cache Go modules\n343: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n344: RUN go mod download\n345: \n346: # Copy source code\n347: COPY cmd/router ./cmd/router\n348: COPY pkg ./pkg\n349: \n350: # Build static binary\n351: RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build \\\n352:     -ldflags=\"-w -s\" \\\n353:     -o /build/router \\\n354:     ./cmd/router\n355: \n356: # Stage 2: Runtime\n357: FROM alpine:3.19 AS runtime\n358: \n359: RUN apk --no-cache add ca-certificates\n360: \n361: WORKDIR /app\n362: \n363: COPY --from=builder /build/router /app/router\n364: \n365: RUN adduser -D -u 1000 router\n366: RUN chown -R router:router /app\n367: \n368: USER router\n369: \n370: EXPOSE 8080\n371: \n372: HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=3s --start-period=5s --retries=3 \\\n373:     CMD wget --no-verbose --tries=1 --spider http://localhost:8080/health || exit 1\n374: \n375: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.title=\"router\"\n376: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.description=\"AgentCube Router component\"\n377: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.vendor=\"AgentCube\"\n378: \n379: ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/router\"]\n380: CMD [\"--port=8080\", \"--debug\"]\n381: ```\n382: \n383: ### Picod Dockerfile\n384: \n385: ```dockerfile\n386: # docker/Dockerfile.picod\n387: # Multi-stage build for Picod\n388: \n389: # Stage 1: Builder\n390: FROM golang:1.21-alpine AS builder\n391: \n392: WORKDIR /build\n393: \n394: COPY go.mod go.sum ./\n395: RUN go mod download\n396: \n397: COPY cmd/picod ./cmd/picod\n398: COPY pkg ./pkg\n399: \n400: RUN CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build \\\n401:     -ldflags=\"-w -s\" \\\n402:     -o /build/picod \\\n403:     ./cmd/picod\n404: \n405: # Stage 2: Runtime\n406: FROM alpine:3.19 AS runtime\n407: \n408: RUN apk --no-cache add ca-certificates\n409: \n410: WORKDIR /app\n411: \n412: COPY --from=builder /build/picod /app/picod\n413: \n414: RUN adduser -D -u 1000 picod\n415: RUN chown -R picod:picod /app\n416: \n417: USER picod\n418: \n419: EXPOSE 8080\n420: \n421: HEALTHCHECK --interval=30s --timeout=3s --start-period=5s --retries=3 \\\n422:     CMD wget --no-verbose --tries=1 --spider http://localhost:8080/health || exit 1\n423: \n424: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.title=\"picod\"\n425: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.description=\"AgentCube Picod component\"\n426: LABEL org.opencontainers.image.vendor=\"AgentCube\"\n427: \n428: ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/picod\"]\n429: CMD [\"--port=8080\"]\n430: ```\n431: \n432: ### .dockerignore\n433: \n434: ```dockerignore\n435: # .dockerignore\n436: # Build context exclusions for efficient Docker builds\n437: \n438: # Version control\n439: .git\n440: .gitignore\n441: \n442: # Build artifacts\n443: bin/\n444: dist/\n445: *.out\n446: coverage.out\n447: \n448: # Dependencies (Go modules cached during build)\n449: vendor/\n450: \n451: # IDE and editor files\n452: .idea/\n453: .vscode/\n454: *.swp\n455: *.swo\n456: *~\n457: \n458: # Documentation\n459: *.md\n460: !README.md\n461: \n462: # Tests\n463: testing/\n464: *_test.go\n465: .pytest_cache/\n466: \n467: # Docker (avoid recursive copy)\n468: docker/\n469: Dockerfile*\n470: \n471: # Kubernetes manifests\n472: manifests/\n473: changes/\n474: \n475: # Python artifacts\n476: __pycache__/\n477: *.pyc\n478: *.pyo\n479: .eggs/\n480: *.egg-info/\n481: \n482: # OS files\n483: .DS_Store\n484: Thumbs.db\n485: \n486: # Logs\n487: *.log\n488: logs/\n489: \n490: # Temporary files\n491: tmp/\n492: temp/\n493: ```\n494: \n495: ---\n496: \n497: ## Makefile Integration\n498: \n499: ### Build Targets\n500: \n501: ```makefile\n502: # Docker configuration\n503: DOCKER_REGISTRY ?= ghcr.io/volcano-sh\n504: DOCKER_TAG ?= latest\n505: VERSION ?= $(shell git describe --tags --always --dirty 2>/dev/null || echo \"dev\")\n506: COMMIT_SHA ?= $(shell git rev-parse --short HEAD 2>/dev/null || echo \"unknown\")\n507: \n508: # Image names\n509: WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/workloadmanager\n510: ROUTER_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/router\n511: PICOD_IMAGE := $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)/picod\n512: \n513: # Build all images\n514: .PHONY: docker-build-all\n515: docker-build-all: docker-build-workloadmanager docker-build-router docker-build-picod\n516: \n517: # Build Workload Manager image\n518: .PHONY: docker-build-workloadmanager\n519: docker-build-workloadmanager:\n520: \t@echo \"Building Workload Manager image...\"\n521: \tdocker build \\\n522: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile \\\n523: \t\t-t $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n524: \t\t-t $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA) \\\n525: \t\t-t $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(VERSION) \\\n526: \t\t.\n527: \t@echo \"✓ Workload Manager image built: $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\"\n528: \n529: # Build Router image\n530: .PHONY: docker-build-router\n531: docker-build-router:\n532: \t@echo \"Building Router image...\"\n533: \tdocker build \\\n534: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.router \\\n535: \t\t-t $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n536: \t\t-t $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA) \\\n537: \t\t-t $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(VERSION) \\\n538: \t\t.\n539: \t@echo \"✓ Router image built: $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\"\n540: \n541: # Build Picod image\n542: .PHONY: docker-build-picod\n543: docker-build-picod:\n544: \t@echo \"Building Picod image...\"\n545: \tdocker build \\\n546: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.picod \\\n547: \t\t-t $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n548: \t\t-t $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA) \\\n549: \t\t-t $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(VERSION) \\\n550: \t\t.\n551: \t@echo \"✓ Picod image built: $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\"\n552: \n553: # Push all images\n554: .PHONY: docker-push-all\n555: docker-push-all: docker-push-workloadmanager docker-push-router docker-push-picod\n556: \n557: # Push Workload Manager image\n558: .PHONY: docker-push-workloadmanager\n559: docker-push-workloadmanager:\n560: \t@echo \"Pushing Workload Manager image to $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)...\"\n561: \tdocker push $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n562: \tdocker push $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA)\n563: \tdocker push $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(VERSION)\n564: \n565: # Push Router image\n566: .PHONY: docker-push-router\n567: docker-push-router:\n568: \t@echo \"Pushing Router image to $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)...\"\n569: \tdocker push $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n570: \tdocker push $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA)\n571: \tdocker push $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(VERSION)\n572: \n573: # Push Picod image\n574: .PHONY: docker-push-picod\n575: docker-push-picod:\n576: \t@echo \"Pushing Picod image to $(DOCKER_REGISTRY)...\"\n577: \tdocker push $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n578: \tdocker push $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA)\n579: \tdocker push $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(VERSION)\n580: \n581: # Load images to Kind cluster\n582: .PHONY: kind-load-all\n583: kind-load-all: kind-load-workloadmanager kind-load-router kind-load-picod\n584: \n585: .PHONY: kind-load-workloadmanager\n586: kind-load-workloadmanager:\n587: \tkind load docker-image $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n588: \n589: .PHONY: kind-load-router\n590: kind-load-router:\n591: \tkind load docker-image $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n592: \n593: .PHONY: kind-load-picod\n594: kind-load-picod:\n595: \tkind load docker-image $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG)\n596: \n597: # Multi-architecture build (requires Docker Buildx)\n598: .PHONY: docker-buildx-all\n599: docker-buildx-all: docker-buildx-workloadmanager docker-buildx-router docker-buildx-picod\n600: \n601: .PHONY: docker-buildx-workloadmanager\n602: docker-buildx-workloadmanager:\n603: \tdocker buildx build \\\n604: \t\t--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n605: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile \\\n606: \t\t-t $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n607: \t\t--push \\\n608: \t\t.\n609: \n610: .PHONY: docker-buildx-router\n611: docker-buildx-router:\n612: \tdocker buildx build \\\n613: \t\t--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n614: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.router \\\n615: \t\t-t $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n616: \t\t--push \\\n617: \t\t.\n618: \n619: .PHONY: docker-buildx-picod\n620: docker-buildx-picod:\n621: \tdocker buildx build \\\n622: \t\t--platform linux/amd64,linux/arm64 \\\n623: \t\t-f docker/Dockerfile.picod \\\n624: \t\t-t $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) \\\n625: \t\t--push \\\n626: \t\t.\n627: \n628: # Clean up local images\n629: .PHONY: docker-clean\n630: docker-clean:\n631: \t-docker rmi $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) 2>/dev/null || true\n632: \t-docker rmi $(WORKLOADMANAGER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA) 2>/dev/null || true\n633: \t-docker rmi $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) 2>/dev/null || true\n634: \t-docker rmi $(ROUTER_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA) 2>/dev/null || true\n635: \t-docker rmi $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(DOCKER_TAG) 2>/dev/null || true\n636: \t-docker rmi $(PICOD_IMAGE):$(COMMIT_SHA) 2>/dev/null || true\n637: ```\n638: \n639: ---\n640: \n641: ## File Structure\n642: \n643: ```\n644: deployment/docker/\n645: ├── Dockerfile                 # Workload Manager image\n646: ├── Dockerfile.router          # Router image\n647: ├── Dockerfile.picod           # Picod image\n648: ├── .dockerignore              # Build context exclusions\n649: ├── design.md                  # This file\n650: ├── delta-spec.md              # Delta specification\n651: └── test/\n652:     ├── build_test.sh          # Build integration tests\n653:     └── runtime_test.sh        # Container runtime tests\n654: ```\n655: \n656: ---\n657: \n658: ## Security Considerations\n659: \n660: ### Principle of Least Privilege\n661: \n662: 1. **Non-root execution:** All containers run as UID 1000 (non-root)\n663: 2. **Minimal capabilities:** No `--cap-add` required\n664: 3. **Read-only root filesystem:** Compatible with `securityContext.readOnlyRootFilesystem: true`\n665: \n666: ### Supply Chain Security\n667: \n668: 1. **Pinned base images:** Use specific versions (`golang:1.21-alpine`, `alpine:3.19`)\n669: 2. **No secrets in images:** Credentials injected via Kubernetes Secrets/Environment\n670: 3. **Reproducible builds:** Static linking with `CGO_ENABLED=0`\n671: \n672: ### Attack Surface Reduction\n673: \n674: 1. **Minimal runtime:** Alpine 3.19 has ~5MB attack surface\n675: 2. **No shell access:** Optional hardening via `rm -rf /bin/sh` in runtime stage\n676: 3. **Static binaries:** No dynamic library vulnerabilities\n677: \n678: ---\n679: \n680: ## Performance Optimization\n681: \n682: ### Build Cache Optimization\n683: \n684: 1. **Layer ordering:** Copy `go.mod`/`go.sum` before source code\n685: 2. **Module caching:** `go mod download` runs before code changes\n686: 3. **Context exclusion:** `.dockerignore` reduces build context size\n687: \n688: ### Image Size Optimization\n689: \n690: 1. **Multi-stage build:** Build tools excluded from runtime\n691: 2. **Static compilation:** No glibc dependencies\n692: 3. **Minimal base:** Alpine 3.19 (~5MB) vs Debian (~100MB)\n693: \n694: Expected image sizes:\n695: - Workload Manager: ~25-35MB\n696: - Router: ~25-35MB\n697: - Picod: ~25-35MB\n698: \n699: ---\n700: \n701: ## Open Questions\n702: \n703: 1. **Multi-architecture support:** Should ARM64 builds be mandatory or optional?\n704: 2. **Distroless migration:** Should we migrate from Alpine to `gcr.io/distroless/static-debian11` for enhanced security?\n705: 3. **Version injection:** Should build version/commit be injected into binaries via `-ldflags`?\n706: 4. **Health check endpoint:** Should HEALTHCHECK use a dedicated endpoint or the main `/health`?\n707: \n708: ---\n709: \n710: ## References\n711: \n712: - `deployment/spec.md` — Deployment Specification\n713: - `deployment/design.md` — Deployment Design\n714: - `docker/delta-spec.md` — Delta Specification for AR-032\n715: - Docker Best Practices: https://docs.docker.com/develop/develop-images/dockerfile_best-practices/\n716: - Alpine Linux: https://alpinelinux.org/\n717: - Multi-stage builds: https://docs.docker.com/build/building/multi-stage/\n718: \n719: (End of file)\n\n(End of file - total 719 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Docker Multi-Stage Build Design — AR-032\n\n**Module:** `docker`  \n**Language:** Dockerfile  \n**Size:** S  \n**Stage:** ST-1 completed\n\n---\n\n## Overview\n\nThis document describes the technical implementation details for Docker multi-stage builds for three AgentCube components: Workload Manager, Router, and picod. The design follows container security best practices, optimizes for minimal image size, and ensures consistency across development, testing, and production environments.\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Multi-Stage Build Pattern\n\nEach component uses a two-stage Dockerfile:","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/deployment/docker/design.md","time":{"start":1775881539446,"end":1775881539470}}}}
