{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775881639265,"sessionID":"ses_285365f84ffeZDEPNqZyERjCgJ","part":{"id":"prt_d7ac9f747001EStrxSHIIjRmFe","messageID":"msg_d7ac9e7e2001KC0K0G16enCVEJ","sessionID":"ses_285365f84ffeZDEPNqZyERjCgJ","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_ba9de5fb3e84432aab22375a","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-032/tasks.md","content":"# AR-032 — Dockerfile 多阶段构建 (3 images) Tasks\n\n**Module:** docker  \n**Language:** Dockerfile  \n**Size:** S  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Workload Manager Dockerfile\n\n- [ ] **T1.1** Create docker/Dockerfile with multi-stage build structure\n  - Set Stage 1: `FROM golang:1.21-alpine AS builder`\n  - Set Stage 2: `FROM alpine:3.19 AS runtime`\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n  - Verify: Both stages are defined with correct base images\n\n- [ ] **T1.2** Configure builder stage workdir and module caching\n  - Set `WORKDIR /build`\n  - Copy `go.mod` and `go.sum` first\n  - Run `go mod download`\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n  - Verify: Go modules cached before source code copy\n\n- [ ] **T1.3** Copy source code for Workload Manager\n  - Copy `cmd/workload-manager` to builder\n  - Copy `pkg` directory to builder\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n  - Verify: Source files available in builder stage\n\n- [ ] **T1.4** Build static Workload Manager binary\n  - Set `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64`\n  - Use `-ldflags=\"-w -s\"` for binary optimization\n  - Output to `/build/workloadmanager`\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n  - Verify: Binary compiled successfully in builder stage\n\n- [ ] **T1.5** Configure runtime stage with CA certificates\n  - Run `apk --no-cache add ca-certificates`\n  - Set `WORKDIR /app`\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n  - Verify: CA certificates installed for HTTPS\n\n- [ ] **T1.6** Copy binary from builder to runtime\n  - Use `COPY --from=builder /build/workloadmanager /app/workloadmanager`\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n  - Verify: Binary present in runtime image\n\n- [ ] **T1.7** Create non-root user for Workload Manager\n  - Create user `apiserver` with UID 1000\n  - Use Alpine `adduser -D -u 1000 apiserver`\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n  - Verify: User created successfully\n\n- [ ] **T1.8** Set file ownership and switch to non-root user\n  - Run `chown -R apiserver:apiserver /app`\n  - Set `USER apiserver`\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n  - Verify: Container runs as non-root (UID 1000)\n\n- [ ] **T1.9** Expose port and configure health check\n  - Add `EXPOSE 8080`\n  - Add HEALTHCHECK with `--interval=30s --timeout=3s --start-period=5s --retries=3`\n  - Health check command: `wget --no-verbose --tries=1 --spider http://localhost:8080/health || exit 1`\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n  - Verify: Port 8080 exposed and health check configured\n\n- [ ] **T1.10** Add OCI labels and entrypoint\n  - Add labels: `org.opencontainers.image.title`, `org.opencontainers.image.description`, `org.opencontainers.image.vendor`\n  - Set `ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/workloadmanager\"]`\n  - Set `CMD [\"--port=8080\"]`\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile`\n  - Verify: Labels present and entrypoint configured\n\n---\n\n## Phase 2: Router Dockerfile\n\n- [ ] **T2.1** Create docker/Dockerfile.router with multi-stage build structure\n  - Set Stage 1: `FROM golang:1.21-alpine AS builder`\n  - Set Stage 2: `FROM alpine:3.19 AS runtime`\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n  - Verify: Both stages defined with correct base images\n\n- [ ] **T2.2** Configure builder stage workdir and module caching\n  - Set `WORKDIR /build`\n  - Copy `go.mod` and `go.sum` first\n  - Run `go mod download`\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n  - Verify: Go modules cached before source code copy\n\n- [ ] **T2.3** Copy source code for Router\n  - Copy `cmd/router` to builder\n  - Copy `pkg` directory to builder\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n  - Verify: Source files available in builder stage\n\n- [ ] **T2.4** Build static Router binary\n  - Set `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64`\n  - Use `-ldflags=\"-w -s\"` for binary optimization\n  - Output to `/build/router`\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n  - Verify: Binary compiled successfully in builder stage\n\n- [ ] **T2.5** Configure runtime stage with CA certificates\n  - Run `apk --no-cache add ca-certificates`\n  - Set `WORKDIR /app`\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n  - Verify: CA certificates installed for HTTPS\n\n- [ ] **T2.6** Copy binary from builder to runtime\n  - Use `COPY --from=builder /build/router /app/router`\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n  - Verify: Binary present in runtime image\n\n- [ ] **T2.7** Create non-root user for Router\n  - Create user `router` with UID 1000\n  - Use Alpine `adduser -D -u 1000 router`\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n  - Verify: User created successfully\n\n- [ ] **T2.8** Set file ownership and switch to non-root user\n  - Run `chown -R router:router /app`\n  - Set `USER router`\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n  - Verify: Container runs as non-root (UID 1000)\n\n- [ ] **T2.9** Expose port and configure health check\n  - Add `EXPOSE 8080`\n  - Add HEALTHCHECK with `--interval=30s --timeout=3s --start-period=5s --retries=3`\n  - Health check command: `wget --no-verbose --tries=1 --spider http://localhost:8080/health || exit 1`\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n  - Verify: Port 8080 exposed and health check configured\n\n- [ ] **T2.10** Add OCI labels and entrypoint\n  - Add labels: `org.opencontainers.image.title`, `org.opencontainers.image.description`, `org.opencontainers.image.vendor`\n  - Set `ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/router\"]`\n  - Set `CMD [\"--port=8080\", \"--debug\"]`\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n  - Verify: Labels present and entrypoint configured\n\n---\n\n## Phase 3: Picod Dockerfile\n\n- [ ] **T3.1** Create docker/Dockerfile.picod with multi-stage build structure\n  - Set Stage 1: `FROM golang:1.21-alpine AS builder`\n  - Set Stage 2: `FROM alpine:3.19 AS runtime`\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n  - Verify: Both stages defined with correct base images\n\n- [ ] **T3.2** Configure builder stage workdir and module caching\n  - Set `WORKDIR /build`\n  - Copy `go.mod` and `go.sum` first\n  - Run `go mod download`\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n  - Verify: Go modules cached before source code copy\n\n- [ ] **T3.3** Copy source code for Picod\n  - Copy `cmd/picod` to builder\n  - Copy `pkg` directory to builder\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n  - Verify: Source files available in builder stage\n\n- [ ] **T3.4** Build static Picod binary\n  - Set `CGO_ENABLED=0 GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64`\n  - Use `-ldflags=\"-w -s\"` for binary optimization\n  - Output to `/build/picod`\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n  - Verify: Binary compiled successfully in builder stage\n\n- [ ] **T3.5** Configure runtime stage with CA certificates\n  - Run `apk --no-cache add ca-certificates`\n  - Set `WORKDIR /app`\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n  - Verify: CA certificates installed for HTTPS\n\n- [ ] **T3.6** Copy binary from builder to runtime\n  - Use `COPY --from=builder /build/picod /app/picod`\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n  - Verify: Binary present in runtime image\n\n- [ ] **T3.7** Create non-root user for Picod\n  - Create user `picod` with UID 1000\n  - Use Alpine `adduser -D -u 1000 picod`\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n  - Verify: User created successfully\n\n- [ ] **T3.8** Set file ownership and switch to non-root user\n  - Run `chown -R picod:picod /app`\n  - Set `USER picod`\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n  - Verify: Container runs as non-root (UID 1000)\n\n- [ ] **T3.9** Expose port and configure health check\n  - Add `EXPOSE 8080`\n  - Add HEALTHCHECK with `--interval=30s --timeout=3s --start-period=5s --retries=3`\n  - Health check command: `wget --no-verbose --tries=1 --spider http://localhost:8080/health || exit 1`\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n  - Verify: Port 8080 exposed and health check configured\n\n- [ ] **T3.10** Add OCI labels and entrypoint\n  - Add labels: `org.opencontainers.image.title`, `org.opencontainers.image.description`, `org.opencontainers.image.vendor`\n  - Set `ENTRYPOINT [\"/app/picod\"]`\n  - Set `CMD [\"--port=8080\"]`\n  - File: `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n  - Verify: Labels present and entrypoint configured\n\n---\n\n## Phase 4: .dockerignore Configuration\n\n- [ ] **T4.1** Create docker/.dockerignore with version control exclusions\n  - Exclude `.git/`, `.gitignore`\n  - File: `docker/.dockerignore`\n  - Verify: Git files excluded from build context\n\n- [ ] **T4.2** Add build artifact exclusions\n  - Exclude `bin/`, `dist/`, `*.out`, `coverage.out`\n  - File: `docker/.dockerignore`\n  - Verify: Build artifacts excluded from context\n\n- [ ] **T4.3** Add test and documentation exclusions\n  - Exclude `testing/`, `*_test.go`, `*.md` (except README.md)\n  - File: `docker/.dockerignore`\n  - Verify: Test files and docs excluded from context\n\n- [ ] **T4.4** Add IDE and development file exclusions\n  - Exclude `.idea/`, `.vscode/`, `*.swp`, `*.swo`, `*~`\n  - Exclude `.pytest_cache/`, `__pycache__/`, `*.pyc`\n  - File: `docker/.dockerignore`\n  - Verify: IDE and Python artifacts excluded\n\n- [ ] **T4.5** Add Docker and manifest exclusions\n  - Exclude `docker/`, `Dockerfile*`, `manifests/`, `changes/`\n  - File: `docker/.dockerignore`\n  - Verify: Docker files and manifests excluded to prevent recursive copy\n\n---\n\n## Phase 5: Makefile Integration\n\n- [ ] **T5.1** Add Docker configuration variables to Makefile\n  - Add `DOCKER_REGISTRY ?= ghcr.io/volcano-sh`\n  - Add `DOCKER_TAG ?= latest`\n  - Add `VERSION`, `COMMIT_SHA` variables\n  - Add image name variables for all three components\n  - File: `Makefile`\n  - Verify: Variables defined correctly\n\n- [ ] **T5.2** Create docker-build-workloadmanager target\n  - Build with `docker/Dockerfile`\n  - Tag with `DOCKER_TAG`, `COMMIT_SHA`, `VERSION`\n  - File: `Makefile`\n  - Verify: `make docker-build-workloadmanager` builds image\n\n- [ ] **T5.3** Create docker-build-router target\n  - Build with `docker/Dockerfile.router`\n  - Tag with `DOCKER_TAG`, `COMMIT_SHA`, `VERSION`\n  - File: `Makefile`\n  - Verify: `make docker-build-router` builds image\n\n- [ ] **T5.4** Create docker-build-picod target\n  - Build with `docker/Dockerfile.picod`\n  - Tag with `DOCKER_TAG`, `COMMIT_SHA`, `VERSION`\n  - File: `Makefile`\n  - Verify: `make docker-build-picod` builds image\n\n- [ ] **T5.5** Create docker-build-all target\n  - Depends on all three build targets\n  - File: `Makefile`\n  - Verify: `make docker-build-all` builds all images sequentially\n\n- [ ] **T5.6** Create push targets for all images\n  - Create `docker-push-workloadmanager`, `docker-push-router`, `docker-push-picod`\n  - Create `docker-push-all` aggregate target\n  - File: `Makefile`\n  - Verify: Push targets use correct registry and tags\n\n- [ ] **T5.7** Create kind-load targets (optional)\n  - Create `kind-load-workloadmanager`, `kind-load-router`, `kind-load-picod`\n  - Create `kind-load-all` aggregate target\n  - File: `Makefile`\n  - Verify: Images loadable to Kind cluster\n\n- [ ] **T5.8** Create docker-clean target\n  - Remove local images with all tags\n  - Use `-` prefix to ignore errors\n  - File: `Makefile`\n  - Verify: `make docker-clean` removes images safely\n\n---\n\n## Phase 6: Dockerfile Validation\n\n- [ ] **T6.1** Build Workload Manager image\n  - Command: `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile -t workloadmanager:test .`\n  - Verify: Build completes without errors\n  - Verify: Image created with tag `workloadmanager:test`\n\n- [ ] **T6.2** Build Router image\n  - Command: `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.router -t router:test .`\n  - Verify: Build completes without errors\n  - Verify: Image created with tag `router:test`\n\n- [ ] **T6.3** Build Picod image\n  - Command: `docker build -f docker/Dockerfile.picod -t picod:test .`\n  - Verify: Build completes without errors\n  - Verify: Image created with tag `picod:test`\n\n- [ ] **T6.4** Verify image sizes under 50MB\n  - Command: `docker images workloadmanager:test router:test picod:test`\n  - Verify: All images < 50MB\n  - Verify: Sizes approximately 25-35MB each\n\n- [ ] **T6.5** Verify non-root user execution\n  - Command: `docker run --rm workloadmanager:test id -u`\n  - Command: `docker run --rm router:test id -u`\n  - Command: `docker run --rm picod:test id -u`\n  - Verify: All return UID 1000 (not root)\n\n- [ ] **T6.6** Verify port 8080 exposed\n  - Command: `docker inspect workloadmanager:test --format='{{.Config.ExposedPorts}}'`\n  - Verify: Port 8080/tcp listed for all images\n\n- [ ] **T6.7** Verify health check configured\n  - Command: `docker inspect workloadmanager:test --format='{{.Config.Healthcheck}}'`\n  - Verify: Health check present with correct intervals\n\n- [ ] **T6.8** Verify OCI labels present\n  - Command: `docker inspect workloadmanager:test --format='{{.Config.Labels}}'`\n  - Verify: Labels include title, description, vendor for all images\n\n- [ ] **T6.9** Verify static binary linkage\n  - Command: `docker run --rm workloadmanager:test /app/workloadmanager --help` (or similar)\n  - Verify: Binary runs without dynamic library errors\n\n- [ ] **T6.10** Verify layer count ≤ 5\n  - Command: `docker history workloadmanager:test`\n  - Verify: Layer count ≤ 5 for all images\n\n---\n\n## Phase 7: Make Target Testing\n\n- [ ] **T7.1** Test docker-build-all target\n  - Command: `make docker-build-all`\n  - Verify: All three images build successfully\n  - Verify: Images tagged with `latest` tag\n\n- [ ] **T7.2** Test docker-build-all with custom tag\n  - Command: `make docker-build-all DOCKER_TAG=v1.0.0`\n  - Verify: Images tagged with `v1.0.0`\n\n- [ ] **T7.3** Test docker-build-all with commit SHA tag\n  - Command: `make docker-build-all COMMIT_SHA=$(git rev-parse --short HEAD)`\n  - Verify: Images tagged with actual commit SHA\n\n- [ ] **T7.4** Test docker-clean target\n  - Command: `make docker-clean`\n  - Verify: Images removed (or error ignored if not present)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 8: Container Runtime Testing (Optional)\n\n- [ ] **T8.1** Test Workload Manager container startup\n  - Command: `docker run -d --name wm-test -p 8080:8080 workloadmanager:test`\n  - Wait 10 seconds for startup\n  - Command: `docker inspect wm-test --format='{{.State.Running}}'`\n  - Verify: Container running\n  - Cleanup: `docker stop wm-test && docker rm wm-test`\n\n- [ ] **T8.2** Test Router container startup\n  - Command: `docker run -d --name router-test -p 8081:8080 -e REDIS_ADDR=redis:6379 router:test`\n  - Wait 10 seconds for startup\n  - Command: `docker inspect router-test --format='{{.State.Running}}'`\n  - Verify: Container running\n  - Cleanup: `docker stop router-test && docker rm router-test`\n\n- [ ] **T8.3** Test Picod container startup\n  - Command: `docker run -d --name picod-test -p 8082:8080 picod:test`\n  - Wait 10 seconds for startup\n  - Command: `docker inspect picod-test --format='{{.State.Running}}'`\n  - Verify: Container running\n  - Cleanup: `docker stop picod-test && docker rm picod-test`\n\n---\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n\n1. ✅ `docker/Dockerfile` — Workload Manager multi-stage build complete\n2. ✅ `docker/Dockerfile.router` — Router multi-stage build complete\n3. ✅ `docker/Dockerfile.picod` — Picod multi-stage build complete\n4. ✅ `docker/.dockerignore` — Build context optimization configured\n5. ✅ All Dockerfiles use `golang:1.21-alpine` as builder base\n6. ✅ All Dockerfiles use `alpine:3.19` as runtime base\n7. ✅ Go modules cached before source code copy (optimization)\n8. ✅ Static binaries compiled with `CGO_ENABLED=0`\n9. ✅ Non-root user (UID 1000) created in all runtime images\n10. ✅ All images expose port 8080\n11. ✅ All images have health check configured\n12. ✅ All images have OCI labels (title, description, vendor)\n13. ✅ All images have correct entrypoint and CMD\n14. ✅ Image sizes under 50MB each\n15. ✅ Layer count ≤ 5 for all images\n16. ✅ Makefile targets for build, push, and clean operations\n17. ✅ `make docker-build-all` builds all three images\n18. ✅ Makefile supports custom DOCKER_TAG and COMMIT_SHA\n19. ✅ `.dockerignore` excludes unnecessary files from build context\n20. ✅ All containers run as non-root user (verified with `id -u`)\n\n---\n\n**Notes:**\n- Stage ST-3: Implementation complete (Dockerfiles and Makefile targets created)\n- Three separate Dockerfiles for three components (Workload Manager, Router, Picod)\n- Multi-stage build pattern: builder (Go) → runtime (Alpine)\n- Security: Non-root execution, minimal base image, static binaries\n- Optimization: Go module caching, `.dockerignore` for context size reduction\n- Expected image sizes: 25-35MB each\n- Makefile integration provides consistent build/push workflow\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-032/tasks.md","exists":false,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-qwen3.5-plus_20260410T163217Z/changes/AR-032/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775881639251,"end":1775881639262}}}}
